== Music ==
The score was created by the French composer [[Laurent Eyquem]]. Choir pieces were recorded in [[Prague]].

== DVD and Blu-ray ==
The German edition of the series was released on 14 May 2014, on DVD and Blu-ray Disc.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.de/s/ref=nb_sb_noss?__mk_de_DE=%C3%85M%C3%85%C5%BD%C3%95%C3%91&url=search-alias%3Ddvd&field-keywords=14%20-%20tageb%C3%BCcher%20des%20ersten%20weltkriegs |title= 14 – Diaries of the Great War|publisher=Amazon DE |accessdate=17 March 2014}}</ref>

== Radio feature ==
Beginning on 9 March 2014 the [[Westdeutscher Rundfunk|WDR]] broadcast a six-part, eponymous Radio Documentary by Christine Sievers and Nicolaus Schröder. This series is based and created in collaboration with the TV series.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wdr5.de/sendungen/tiefenblick/vierzehntagebuecher100.html|title=Hördokumentation im WDR|accessdate=18 March 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150128132734/http://www.wdr5.de/sendungen/tiefenblick/vierzehntagebuecher100.html|archivedate=28 January 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref>

== Accompanying books ==
The series is accompanied by a coffee table book, which is being published by [[BBC Books]] in the United Kingdom, and [[Bucher Verlag]] in Germany. In eight chapters, the book presents high resolution photographs, which were colorized prior and during World War I. Each photo is accompanied by a diary quote. The foreword is written by [[Peter Englund]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bucher-verlag.de/news-3622-134-145-begleitbuch_zur_tv_doku_14_tagebuecher_des_ersten_weltkriegs_auf_arte_und_im_ersten.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140408220200/http://www.bucher-verlag.de/news-3622-134-145-begleitbuch_zur_tv_doku_14_tagebuecher_des_ersten_weltkriegs_auf_arte_und_im_ersten.html|dead-url=yes|archive-date=8 April 2014|title=Accompanying Coffee Table Book|accessdate=19 March 2014}}</ref>

The accompanying book "14 - Der große Krieg" by Oliver Janz was published in October 2013 by Campus Verlag.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.campus.de/buecher-campus-verlag/wirtschaft-gesellschaft/wissen/14_der_grosse_krieg-4117.html|title=Begleitbuch von Oliver Janz|accessdate=27 April 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140823045749/http://www.campus.de/buecher-campus-verlag/wirtschaft-gesellschaft/wissen/14_der_grosse_krieg-4117.html|archivedate=23 August 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref>

== Accompanying exhibition ==

The [[Bundeswehr Military History Museum|Military History Museum]] [[Dresden]] shows in a special exhibition "14-Menschen-Krieg" from 01. August 2014 until 24. February 2015 all 14 biographies and their perspectives on World War I. The exhibition focuses on the eve of the war and furthermore shows the dimension and forms of sufferings of both, soldiers and civilians. The exhibition draws a conclusion of World War I and ends with a forecast on the soon to follow World War II.
<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mhmbw.de/sonderausstellungen/14-menschen-krieg|title=Sonderausstellung zum Thema im Militärhistorischen Museum in Dresden|accessdate=18 May 2014|archive-url=https://archive.is/20140318030654/http://www.mhmbw.de/sonderausstellungen/14-menschen-krieg|archive-date=18 March 2014|dead-url=yes|df=dmy-all}}</ref>

== Reception ==

=== Critical response ===

The series received very positive reviews. [[Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung]] called it "Gripping, emotional, and real. A milestone for European television.".<ref>{{cite news | first=Lorenz | last=Jäger | title=Weltkriegsgedenken auf Arte - Jede Szene findet eine Parallele beim Feind | work=Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung | url=http://www.faz.net/aktuell/feuilleton/medien/weltkriegsgedenken-auf-arte-jede-szene-findet-eine-parallele-beim-feind-12914544.html | date=29 April 2014 | accessdate=30 April 2014 }}</ref> [[Süddeutsche Zeitung]] describes the series as "A story of the destruction and the future of television.".<ref>{{cite news | first=Claudia | last=Tieschky | title=Requiem | work=Süddeutsche Zeitung |date=2014-04-29 }}</ref> [[Stuttgarter Zeitung]] calls it "Woven together like a modern television series.".<ref>{{cite news | first=Ulla | last=Hanselmann | title=Mit emotionaler Wucht in die Vergangenheit |work=Stuttgarter Zeitung | date=29 April 2014 }}</ref> [[Neue Zürcher Zeitung]] says that "the program manages to fascinate by combining different observations, in different locations, and managing to condense these into a coherent mood.".<ref>{{cite news | first=Claudia | last=Schwartz | title=Sag zum Abschied nicht Adieu | work=Neue Zürcher Zeitung |date=2014-04-29 }}</ref> [[Le Monde]] ascribes to the series "a never before seen virtuosity",<ref>{{cite news | first=Philippe-Jean | last=Catinchi | title=Correspondances de guerre | work=Le Monde | date=27 April 2014 }}</ref> while Direct Matin calls it "of exceptional quality."<ref>{{cite news | title=La guerre de l'intérieur | work=Direct Matin | date=29 April 2014 }}</ref> The Dutch version of the series was described as follows by [[NRC Handelsblad]]: "Phantastic Television Making… We ride a rollercoaster of emotions, as if we are not supposed to understand history but rather to live it ourselves."<ref>{{cite news | first=Hans | last=Beerekamp | title=Beleef de Grote Oorlog met Marina en Käthe | work=NRC Handelsblad | date=14 April 2014 | url=http://www.nrc.nl/handelsblad/van/2014/april/14/beleef-de-grote-oorlog-met-marina-en-kathe-1367467 | accessdate=14 April 2014 }}</ref> After watching the series on [[Netflix]], [[William F.B. O'Reilly]] called the series "superbly done" and said "unlike other Netflix programming that escapes the mind moments after consumption, "14" lingers. It consumes its viewers rather than the other way around."<ref>{{cite news | first=William | last=O'Reilly | title=War-weary Europe is putty to Putin | publisher=[[Newsday]] | url=http://www.newsday.com/opinion/columnists/william-f-b-o-reilly/war-weary-europe-is-putty-to-putin-william-f-b-o-reilly-1.9935420 | date=13 February 2015 | accessdate=26 February 2015 }}</ref>

